argin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" spaceabove="8.0" spacebelow="8.0" style="default"><Font executable="false" style="Text">All solutions must be found using Maple.</Font></Text-field><Text-field alignment="left" bullet="none" firstindent="0.0" layout="default" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" spaceabove="8.0" spacebelow="8.0" style="default"><Font background="[0,0,0]" family="Lucida Bright">This exercise uses<Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="true" family="Lucida Bright"> plot, fieldplot, int</Font><Font background="[0,0,0]" family="Lucida Bright">.</Font></Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1">First things first.</Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">The first thing you should do with Maple is load in the packages you will need.  There's no harm in being careful and loading in things that you think you might need, even if you do not use them.</Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">with(LinearAlgebra):</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">with(plots):</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group></Section><Text-field/><Text-field/><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1">Problems.</Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Group><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">Consider the vector field <Equation executable="true" input-equation="f := &lt; -y/(x^2+y^2), x/(x^2+y^2) &gt;" style="2D Input">NiM+SSJmRzYiLUkkPCw+R0YlNiQsJComSSJ5R0YlIiIiLCYqJEkieEdGJSIiI0YsKiRGK0YwRiwhIiJGMjYjKiZGL0YsRi1GMg==</Equation><Font executable="true">.</Font></Text-field></Group><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">1.  Does this field have a potential?  Why?</Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Group><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">2. Using path integrals calculate  <Equation executable="true" input-equation="int(f(r), r)" style="2D Input">NiMtSSRpbnRHNiRJKnByb3RlY3RlZEdGJkkoX3N5c2xpYkc2IjYkLUkiZkdGKDYjSSJyR0YoRi0=</Equation><Font italic="false" style="Maple Input" underline="false"> </Font>around a closed circle of radius one centered at (2,0) oriented anti-clockwise.<Font executable="false">  Plot the vector field and the path of integration.  </Font>Explain your result with regard to your answer to question 1.</Text-field></Group><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">3. <Font executable="false">Using path integrals calculate  </Font><Equation executable="true" style="2D Input">NiMtSSRpbnRHNiRJKnByb3RlY3RlZEdGJkkoX3N5c2xpYkc2IjYkLUkiZkdGKDYjSSJyR0YoRi0=</Equation><Font executable="false"> around a closed circle of radius one centered at (0,0) oriented anti-clockwise.  Plot the vector field and the path of integration.  Explain your result with regard to your answer to question 1.</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"><Font executable="false">4. Using path integrals calculate  </Font><Equation executable="true" style="2D Input">NiMtSSRpbnRHNiRJKnByb3RlY3RlZEdGJkkoX3N5c2xpYkc2IjYkLUkiZkdGKDYjSSJyR0YoRi0=</Equation><Font executable="false"> around a closed circle of radius one centered at (0,0) oriented anti-clockwise, traversing the loop twice.  Explain your result with regard to your answer to question 1.</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">5. Use Maple (int) to find the potential for the vector field.  Can you find more than one potential?  Explain your results to questions 2-5 in light of the properties of this function.</Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/></Section><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/></Worksheet>